&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INFORMATION ANALYST ADVERT – Band 5 Permanent Post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen in an Information Analyst role based at the South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust’s Information Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be part of a highly skilled team helping to deliver a professional information service to the Trust. This includes producing information to meet reporting requirements of NHS England, to develop performance management and for commissioning organisations; as well as supporting the Trust’s own internal information requirements. This role is currently focused on the emergency division, though you may be asked to provide support across any area of the Trusts information requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primarily the post holder will be responsible for ensuring that the Trust’s central returns are completed to a high standard and are submitted in a timely manner. There will be further opportunities to produce information and analysis to answer ad-hoc queries and requests that come into the Information Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be given support to help develop their technical skills and analytical abilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ideally you will have:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working within an NHS environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working with NHS data sets and knowledge of NHS mandatory reporting requirements, any knowledge of NHS data standards would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience and knowledge of MS Excel and/or SQL server skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication skills and analytical skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Organised and able to prioritise to meet tight deadlines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRichard HoweJob titleBusiness Information ManagerEmail addressrichard.howe@swft.nhs.ukTelephone number01926 495321 ext. 3032&lt;/p&gt;
